reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Dr. Carter explains concepts very clearly and makes difficult topics easy to understand. Highly recommend!

reviews.subject: Calculus
reviews.review: Good professor, but sometimes the lectures can be a bit fast-paced. Make sure to review the material after class.

reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: The course was interesting, but Dr. Martinez's teaching style is a bit monotonous. Could use more engagement in class.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Not the best at explaining concepts, and the lectures are often unorganized. I struggled to follow along.

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Amazing professor! Very knowledgeable and approachable. The assignments were challenging but rewarding.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Prof. Davis makes history come alive with his engaging stories. However, the reading workload can be heavy.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Wilson's passion for literature is infectious. She encourages deep analysis and class discussions.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: The lectures are informative, but sometimes lack structure. Prof. Taylor could improve his presentation skills.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Dr. Lee is very engaging and provides real-world examples to explain theories. The class is interesting, but the exams are tough.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Difficult to follow lectures. The material is complex, and Prof. Walker does not provide enough support for students.

reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Great professor with clear explanations. However, the pace of the class is quite fast, so keep up with the homework.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Interesting discussions in class, but the lectures can be dry. Prof. Harris is knowledgeable but not very engaging.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Dr. Robinson is a fantastic professor who makes you think critically about complex topics. Highly recommended.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Very passionate about art history. Prof. Thompson's classes are enjoyable, but the exams are quite challenging.

reviews.subject: Statistics
reviews.review: The subject matter is difficult, and Dr. White's teaching style doesn't make it any easier. Be prepared to study a lot.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Prof. King is an amazing professor who truly cares about the environment. His lectures are informative and inspiring.

reviews.subject: Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. Scott's classes are engaging and thought-provoking. The course material is fascinating, but the grading is strict.

reviews.subject: Music Theory
reviews.review: Prof. Lewis is knowledgeable, but his lectures can be hard to follow. The course requires a lot of practice outside class.

reviews.subject: Marketing
reviews.review: Dr. Adams provides great insights into the marketing world. The class projects are practical but demanding.

reviews.subject: Ethics
reviews.review: Prof. Moore encourages deep thinking and ethical discussions. His classes are always engaging and intellectually stimulating.
